# <type>: <imperative summary>
#
# Use Conventional Commit prefixes such as fix:, perf:, docs:, test:, chore:.
# Keep the subject focused on the user-visible or operational change.
#
# Required for fix: commits that touch production behavior:
#
# Root cause:
# - What failed, drifted, or was missing?
#
# Behavior changed:
# - What will production do differently after this commit?
#
# Verification:
# - Which test, smoke check, prod read-only check, or log review proves it?
#
# Deployment/rollback:
# - Note migrations, config, queues, cron changes, cache clears, or rollback notes.
